ed%20them%20on%20purpose%20because%20I%20am%20not%20good%20enough%20to%20care%20for%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20were%20used%20as%20evidence%20during%20Letby's%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELetby%20was%20convicted%20in%202023%20for%20the%20murder%20of%20seven%20babies%20and%20the%20attempted%20murder%20of%20six%20others%2C%20including%20two%20attempts%20on%20one%20child.%20Earlier%20this%20year%2C%20she%20proclaimed%20her%20innocence%20while%20receiving%20an%20additional%20whole-life%20sentence%20for%20the%20attempted%20murder%20of%20another%20baby%20girl.%20She%20is%20currently%20serving%2015%20whole-life%20sentences%20for%20her%20crimes%2C%20committed%20at%20the%20Countess%20of%20Chester%20Hospital's%20neonatal%20unit%20between%20June%202015%20and%20June%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2F7tmm299o_lucy-letby-note-i-am-evil_625x300_19_August_23.jpg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESources%20close%20to%20the%20case%20told%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2C%20noindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fuk-news%2Farticle%2F2024%2Fsep%2F03%2Fi-am-evil-i-did-this-lucy-letbys-so-called-confessions-were-written-on-advice-of-counsellors%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Guardian%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3Ethat%20the%20notes%2C%20labelled%20as%20confessions%2C%20were%20produced%20as%20part%20of%20a%20therapeutic%20process%20during%20counselling%20sessions.%20Letby%20was%20reportedly%20advised%20to%20document%20her%20troubling%20thoughts%20and%20feelings%20to%20cope%20with%20intense%20stress.%20The%20notes%2C%20written%20after%20some%20of%20her%20colleagues%20began%20suspecting%20her%20of%20murder%2C%20included%20references%20to%20her%20family%2C%20pets%2C%20and%20coworkers%2C%20and%20described%20recurring%20suicidal%20thoughts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20prosecution%20built%20its%20case%20against%20Letby%20by%20highlighting%20incriminating%20phrases%20like%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20evil%20I%20did%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20were%20repeatedly%20brought%20to%20the%20jury's%20attention.%20However%2C%20other%20phrases%20in%20the%20notes%2C%20which%20were%20also%20considered%20confessions%2C%20included%20statements%20like%20%26quot%3BWhy%20me%3F%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20haven't%20done%20anything%20wrong%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BPolice%20investigation%20slander%20discrimination%20victimisation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20experts%20have%20dismissed%20Letby's%20notes%20as%20%26quot%3Bmeaningless%26quot%3B%20and%20argued%20they%20held%20no%20value%20as%20evidence%2C%20especially%20if%20written%20as%20part%20of%20therapy.%20David%20Wilson%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20criminology%20at%20Birmingham%20City%20University%2C%20commented%2C%20%26quot%3BMany%20people%20say%20things%20under%20stress%20that%20may%20imply%20one%20thing%20but%20mean%20nothing%2C%20other%20than%20reflecting%20their%20underlying%20stress.%26quot%3B%20He%20added%20that%20if%20the%20notes%20were%20part%20of%20therapy%2C%20they%20should%20not%20be%20considered%20confessions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERichard%20Curen%2C%20chair%20of%20the%20Forensic%20Psychotherapy%20Society%2C%20echoed%20this%20sentiment%2C%20stating%20that%20%26quot%3Bdoodling%20and%20journaling%20are%20ways%20to%20take%20control%20of%20one's%20thoughts%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20do%20not%20indicate%20a%20confession.%20He%20noted%20that%20Letby's%20response%20about%20the%20notes%20in%20court%20was%20%26quot%3Brobust%26quot%3B%20and%20aligned%20with%20her%20explanation%20that%20she%20was%20expressing%20how%20she%20felt%20she%20was%20being%20perceived.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20public%20inquiry%20into%20Letby's%20case%20is%20set%20to%20begin%20next%20week%20amid%20growing%20questions%20about%20the%20safety%20of%20her%20conviction.%20Sources%20revealed%20that%20Kathryn%20de%20Beger%2C%20the%20head%20of%20occupational%20health%20and%20wellbeing%20at%20the%20hospital%20where%20Letby%20worked%2C%20had%20encouraged%20her%20to%20write%20down%20her%20feelings%20to%20cope%20with%20extreme%20stress.%20Letby's%20Chester%20GP%20also%20advised%20her%20to%20write%20down%20thoughts%20she%20found%20difficult%20to%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELetby%20had%20received%20several%20counselling%20sessions%20from%20Ms.%20de%20Beger%2C%20and%20her%20notes%20frequently%20referenced%20her.%20During%20her%20trial%2C%20Letby%20explained%20that%20she%20had%20always%20written%20things%20down%20to%20help%20understand%20her%20feelings%2C%20describing%20the%20notes%20as%20random%20thoughts.%20She%20questioned%20herself%2C%20wondering%20if%20she%20had%20unintentionally%20caused%20harm%20by%20not%20being%20knowledgeable%20enough%20or%20by%20not%20being%20a%20good%20enough%20nurse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20defence%2C%20it%20was%20argued%20that%20the%20notes%20reflected%20her%20distressed%20state%20of%20mind%20after%20being%20accused%20of%20killing%20babies%2C%20rather%20than%20an%20admission%20of%20guilt.%20Her%20defence%20barrister%2C%20Ben%20Myers%20KC%2C%20previously%20argued%20that%20the%20prosecution's%20case%20was%20%26quot%3Briddled%20with%20guilt%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20everything%20Letby%20said%20or%20did%20was%20interpreted%20as%20evidence%20of%20her%20guilt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20this%2C%20no%20expert%20forensic%20psychologists%20were%20called%20to%20testify%20on%20how%20the%20notes%20should%20be%20interpreted.%20The%20Countess%20of%20Chester%20Hospital%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20case%20while%20the%20inquiry%20and%20further%20investigations%20are%20ongoing.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725474960000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fbr77oh3s_lucy-letby-afp_625x300_19_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fi-am-evil-i-did-this-uks-baby