onstituencies.%20The%20list%20includes%20the%20names%20of%20Chief%20Minister%20Nayab%20Singh%20Saini%2C%20who%20will%20be%20contesting%20from%20the%20Ladwa%20constituency%2C%20and%20former%20minister%20Anil%20Vij.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Vij%20will%20be%20the%20BJP's%20candidate%20from%20the%20Ambala%20Cantonment%20constituency%2C%20a%20seat%20he%20has%20won%20three%20successive%20times%20since%202009.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Saini%2C%20who%20was%20an%20MP%20from%20Kurukshetra%20until%20he%20replaced%20Manohar%20Lal%20Khattar%20as%20the%20Haryana%20chief%20minister%20in%20March%20this%20year%2C%20currently%20represents%20the%20Karnal%20Assembly%20seat%2C%20which%20he%20won%20in%20a%20bypoll%20in%20June.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20candidates%20include%20Ambala%20Mayor%20and%20former%20Union%20Minister%20Vinod%20Sharma's%20wife%20Shakti%20Rani%20Sharma%2C%20who%20will%20be%20contesting%20from%20the%20Kalka%20assembly%20constituency.%20Ms%20Sharma%20is%20the%20mother%20of%20Manu%20Sharma%2C%20a%20convict%20in%20the%20Jessica%20Lal%20murder%20case.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShruti%20Choudhry%20who%20left%20the%20Congress%20and%20joined%20the%20BJP%20with%20her%20mother%20-%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%20Kiran%20Choudhry%20-%20in%20June%20has%20been%20given%20a%20ticket%20from%20Tosham.%20Three%20former%20legislators%20from%20the%20Jannayak%20Janata%20Party%2C%20which%20was%20the%20BJP's%20ally%20until%20this%20year%2C%20have%20also%20been%20fielded.%20These%20are%20Devender%20Singh%20Babli%20from%20Tohana%2C%20Ram%20Kumar%20Gautam%20from%20Safidon%20and%20Anoop%20Dhanak%20from%20Uklana.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20other%20inclusions%20are%20Deepak%20Hooda%2C%20who%20has%20been%20the%20captain%20of%20the%20Indian%20Kabaddi%20team%2C%20from%20Meham%20and%20Union%20Minister%20Om%20Prakash%20Dhankar%2C%20who%20will%20be%20contesting%20from%20Badli.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20list%20includes%20eight%20women%2C%2013%20leaders%20from%20the%20Scheduled%20Castes%20and%20nine%20from%20other%20backward%20communities%20(OBCs).%20The%20party%20has%20also%20dropped%20some%20MLAs%2C%20including%20some%20ministers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMP%20Naveen%20Jindal's%20mother%2C%20Savitri%20Jindal%2C%20who%20was%20widely%20expected%20to%20get%20a%20ticket%20from%20Hisar%2C%20has%20not%20made%20the%20cut%20and%20the%20party%20has%20decided%20to%20stick%20with%20the%20incumbent%2C%20Kamal%20Gupta%2C%20who%20is%20also%20a%20state%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20upcoming%20elections%20in%20Haryana%20will%20be%20crucial%20for%20the%20BJP%2C%20especially%20because%20it%20won%20only%20five%20of%20the%20state's%2010%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20after%20sweeping%20all%20of%20them%20in%202019.%20It%20will%20be%20an%20opportunity%20for%20the%20party%20to%20prove%20that%20it%20remains%20popular%20with%20voters%20after%20failing%20-%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%2010%20years%20-%20to%20achieve%20a%20majority%20on%20its%20own%20in%20the%20general%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%2C%20which%20is%20seen%20to%20be%20gaining%20ground%20in%20the%20state%2C%20is%20also%20likely%20to%20pose%20a%20challenge%20and%20could%20emerge%20stronger%20if%20its%20alliance%20talks%20with%20INDIA%20partner%20AAP%20are%20successful.%20The%20party%20believes%20it%20has%20a%20strong%20chance%20of%20dislodging%20the%20BJP%2C%20which%20has%20ruled%20Haryana%20since%202014.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaryana%20will%20vote%20on%20October%205%20and%20counting%20will%20be%20held%20on%20October%208.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725470760000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2Foq69kgu8_nayab-singh-saini-nayab-saini_625x300_27_October_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbjp-names-67-candidates-in-first-list-for-haryana-assembly-elections-chief-minister-to-contest-from-ladwa-6490866%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Looking%20to%20get%20the%20first-mover%20advantage%20in%20the%20Haryana%20Assemb