20of%20a%20challenge%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bchroming%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20collapsed%20at%20his%20home%20in%20Doncaster%2C%20South%20Yorkshire%2C%20on%20August%2021%2C%20reported%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2C%20noindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmetro.co.uk%2F2024%2F09%2F02%2Fboy-12-narrowly-survives-deadly-social-media-challenge-goes-wrong-21534581%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EMetro%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20mother%2C%20Nichola%20King%2C%20who%20had%20just%20finished%20breastfeeding%20her%20youngest%20child%20upstairs%2C%20was%20alarmed%20by%20a%20loud%20thud%20and%20rushed%20downstairs%20to%20investigate.%20The%2036-year-old%20was%20horrified%20to%20find%20her%20son%20having%20a%20seizure%20on%20the%20kitchen%20floor%20before%20he%20went%20into%20cardiac%20arrest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENichola's%20eldest%20son%2C%20Kaiden%2C%20immediately%20called%20999%20while%20Nichola%20performed%20CPR%20on%20Cesar%20as%20they%20awaited%20the%20ambulance.%20Cesar%20was%20rushed%20to%20the%20hospital%2C%20where%20he%20was%20placed%20in%20a%20medically%20induced%20coma%20for%20two%20days%20after%20experiencing%20further%20seizures%20and%20cardiac%20arrests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFortunately%2C%20Cesar%20recovered%20and%20is%20now%20back%20home%2C%20but%20Nichola%2C%20a%20mother%20of%20four%2C%20has%20shared%20photos%20of%20her%20son%20receiving%20CPR%20and%20in%20intensive%20care%20to%20warn%20others%20about%20the%20dangers%20of%20chroming.%20The%20trend%20involves%20inhaling%20toxic%20chemicals%20from%20substances%20like%20paint%2C%20solvents%2C%20aerosol%20cans%2C%20cleaning%20products%2C%20or%20petrol%20to%20achieve%20a%20brief%20'high.'%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20practice%20can%20cause%20slurred%20speech%2C%20dizziness%2C%20hallucinations%2C%20nausea%2C%20and%20disorientation%2C%20but%20it%20can%20also%20lead%20to%20heart%20attacks%20or%20suffocation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecalling%20the%20moment%20she%20heard%20her%20son%20collapse%2C%20Nichola%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20just%20finished%20breastfeeding%20my%20baby%20and%20was%20drifting%20off%20to%20sleep%20when%20I%20heard%20a%20really%20loud%20bang.%20I%20thought%20one%20of%20the%20kids%20had%20done%20something.%20I%20heard%20Cesar%20creeping%20downstairs%20and%20assumed%20he%20was%20getting%20something%20to%20eat.%20The%20bang%20sounded%20like%20someone%20had%20fallen%20over.%20I%20heard%20a%20moaning%20sound%20from%20downstairs%20and%20thought%20Cesar%20had%20broken%20a%20bone%20or%20something.%20When%20I%20went%20downstairs%2C%20I%20saw%20him%20lying%20on%20the%20floor%2C%20and%20his%20eyes%20were%20rolling%20back%20into%20his%20head.%20It%20was%20terrifying.%20He%20was%20having%20a%20seizure.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENichola%20ran%20upstairs%20to%20grab%20her%20phone%2C%20but%20her%20hands%20were%20shaking%20so%20much%20she%20couldn't%20unlock%20it%2C%20so%20she%20asked%20her%20eldest%20to%20call%20an%20ambulance.%20She%20then%20began%20performing%20CPR%20on%20Cesar%20to%20try%20to%20restore%20his%20breathing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20thought%20he'd%20fallen%20and%20hit%20his%20head.%20I%20had%20no%20idea%20what%20had%20happened.%20He%20turned%20blue%20and%20stopped%20breathing.%20I%20thought%20he'd%20died.%20I%20was%20in%20complete%20shock.%20I%20watched%20my%20son%20die%20and%20saw%20the%20light%20go%20out%20of%20his%20eyes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Cesar%20was%20taken%20to%20Doncaster%20Royal%20Infirmary%2C%20police%20informed%20Nichola%20that%20they%20had%20found%20a%20can%20of%20Aldi%20Lacura%20deodorant%20and%20other%20chroming%20paraphernalia%20on%20the%20kitchen%20floor%2C%20leading%20them%20to%20believe%20Cesar%20had%20inhaled%20the%20deodorant%20before%20losing%20consciousness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENichola%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20hadn't%20heard%20of%20chroming%20before%20this.%20An%20older%20boy%20had%20shown%20him%20how%20to%20do%20it.%20When%20police%20told%20me%20what%20he'd%20inhaled%2C%20I%20thought%20he%20was%20going%20to%20die.%20I%20knew%20the%20warnings%20on%20the%20back%20of%20the%20cans%20that%20say%20'solvent%20abuse%20kills%20instantly.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECesar%20was%20later%20transferred%20to%20Sheffield%20Children's%20Hospital%2C%20where%20he%20was%20kept%20in%20a%20medically%20induced%20coma%20for%2048%20hours.%20When%20he%20came%20out%20of%20the%20coma%2C%20he%20began%20showing%20signs%20of%20progress%2C%20soon%20breathing%20on%20his%20own%20and%20able%20to%20talk%20and%20walk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20eight%20days%20in%20the%20hospital%2C%20Cesar%20was%20discharged%20and%20allowed%20to%20return%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENichola%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20over%20the%20moon.%20He%20was%20almost%20back%20to%20normal%20when%20he%20was%20discharged-eating%2C%20drinking%2C%20having%20a%20laugh.%20He%20just%20feels%20tired.%20We%20don't%20know%20about%20long-term%20damage%2C%20but%20his%20short-term%20memory%20is%20very%20bad.%20He%20couldn't%20remember%20what%20had%20happened.%20If%20I%20hadn't%20heard%20something%20that%20night%2C%20I%20would%20have%20found%20a%20dead%20body%20the%20next%20morning.%20I've%20spoken%20to%20Cesar%20and%20asked%20him%20never%20to%20do%20anything%20like%20this%20again.%20I've%20thrown%20out%20everything%20in%20the%20house%20that%20sprays.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENichola%20also%20wants%20to%20warn%20other%20children%20who%20might%20be%20tempted%20to%20try%20chroming%3A%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20worth%20it.%20It%20might%20feel%20good%2C%20but%20it%20definitely%20doesn't%20when%20you're%20in%20the%20hospital%20struggling%20to%20breathe%20and%20causing%20pain%20to%20your%20parents.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20also%20want%20to%20stress%20the%20importance%20of%20parents%20being%20trained%20in%20first%20aid.%20I%20believe%20anyone%20with%20kids%20should%20attend%20a%20course%2C%20as%20it%20could%20be%20the%20difference%20between%20life%20and%20death.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22pu